			<ns0:name>k...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/114701340294105671768/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">One of the tests (sigpipe_test) actually hangs under valgrind because of this bug: 
The uninitialized 4 bytes in the IOVec struct get non-zero value and recvmsg thinks 
that iov_len is 545460847616 (which is our expected 32-bit len value plus garbage). 

We are simply (un)lucky that thus does not fail when running natively. </ns0:content><ns0:updated>2010-03-18T15:08:26.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2010-03-18T15:08:26.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 4 by k...@google.com</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=356#c4" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/356/comments/full/4" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>